{{sectionHeading "intlNumber"}}

<h3>Example</h3>

<p>Template String:</p>
{{#code "generic"}}
{{{examples.number.source}}}
{{/code}}

<p>Context Object:</p>
{{#code "js"}}
var context = {
    intl: {
        locale: "de-DE"
    },
    amount: 15000
};
{{/code}}

<p>Rendered Output:</p>
<div class="example">
    {{{examples.number.rendered}}}
</div>

<p>Use the {{code "intlNumber"}} helper to format numbers, currencies and percentages for different locales. Remember to use the {{code "{{#intl}}"}} helper to properly set any custom number or currency formats, or locales you wish to use.</p>

<h3>Required Parameter</h3>
<dl class="parameters-list">
    <dt>{{code "value: Number"}}</dt>
    <dd>The value of the number that you wish to format.</dd>
</dl>

<h3>Hash Arguments (optional)</h3>
<dl class="parameters-list">
    <dt>{{code "style: String"}}</dt>
    <dd>Set to either {{code "'currency'"}} or {{code "'percent'"}}, depending on your preferred style. Not setting this parameter will render the value as a normal number.</dd>

    <dt>{{code "currency: String"}}<dt>
    <dd>The type of currency that should be used to render the number.</dd>
</dl>


